Azure Blob Storage is used for storing massive amounts of unstructured data such as text, images, and videos.

It supports:

* Block blobs (documents, media)
* Append blobs (logs)
* Page blobs (VM disks)

For example, storing images for a website.

A real-life use case is video streaming platforms.

Another example is backup and archival systems.

Blob storage is highly scalable and cost-effective.
